oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Ricky Skaggs Pickin' Party at Wolftrap (1991)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Skaggs, Ricky; Monroe, Bill, 1911-1996; Stanley, Ralph;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Three color window card (black and red on yellow) announcing The Ricky Skaggs Pickin' Party, a bluegrass spectacular, starring Ricky Skaggs and featuring Bill Monroe and The Bluegrass Boys, Ralph Stanley and The Clinch Mountain Boys, Alison Krauss and Union Station, Tony Rice Unit, and a reunion performance by The New South with J. D. Crowe, Tony Rice, Jerry Douglas, and Ricky Skaggs at Wolf Trap on August 25. Poster features a metal photoplate of a chicken and the phrase, "something to crow about!"
